In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 11th, 2015 as Veterans Day. He praises the strength and selflessness of the men and women in the US military and emphasizes the importance of taking care of veterans and their families. The Obama Administration has made efforts to support veterans by helping them transition to civilian jobs, providing education benefits, and improving access to healthcare. The First Lady's Joining Forces initiative aims to end veterans' homelessness. President Obama also mentions the Clay Hunt Suicide Prevention for American Veterans Act, which addresses mental health care for veterans. He calls on Americans to show gratitude and support for veterans, and encourages public ceremonies and private prayers to honor them.